  "text": "Okay and Sevin (2011a,b) studied the effect of irrigation on some pistachio fruit characteristics and concluded that differences among cultivars were more significant under non-irrigated conditions. Irrigation increased kernel weight but did not have a significant impact on shell and kernel colours [CITATION_1] . [CITATION_2] showed that the more severe the water stress level achieved during stage II, the harder and crunchier the resulting pistachios.",
